# Auto commit and push

After finishing a task that changes project files, **always commit and push to `origin`** without waiting for the user to ask.

Follow the existing git safety protocol:
- Never update git config
- Never force-push to main/master
- Never use destructive git commands unless explicitly requested
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, etc.)
- Use a concise commit message focused on why
- Stage only relevant files, then `git push -u origin HEAD`
- If there is nothing to commit, skip the empty commit but still push if the branch is ahead

Do this at the end of each completed change set in the same turn when practical.
